Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.82,0:12:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This red horse, that is supposed to bring prosperous business...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what caused he first fire in Rizencho,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but this horse was found at the site of the fire because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.70,0:12:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,e Owner oe use was a good customer of Mr. Genda's store...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.70,0:12:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Genda probably gave that person this key holder inside a box...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.64,0:12:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before the person opened the box, the house caught fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.68,0:12:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The box and Kanu both burned leaving behind only the Red Rabbit Horse .
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course the owner of the house would have no knowledge of the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Red Horse is a code word for the police meaning arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.29,0:12:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the press began making a fuss writing articles
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.06,0:12:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,such as "The Start of a Series of Arsons. "...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.99,0:12:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Genda who was shocked at hearing the person saying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.67,0:12:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she knew nothing about the horse that he gave her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.90,0:12:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,got worried that his sleepwalking habit when he was a child had occurred again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.51,0:12:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went to your hospital, where he was taken advantage of!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.88,0:12:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, when you heard Genda's story.\NYou made him believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.45,0:12:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he was a sleepwalker who had a habit of committing arsons...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.45,0:13:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and took note of the fact that the first fire occurred in 1 chome.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.92,0:13:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then after, you set fire to\N2-chome and 3-chome in order...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You burned your house on 4 chome,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.96,0:13:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and killed your wife, Ryoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.23,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cut the Kanu and stand off the key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and left the red horse at the site of the fire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.14,0:13:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like the serial arsonist did it, and framed Mr. Genda up as the arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.91,0:13:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made a spare key for this house and snuck in here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.71,0:13:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,night after night to corner\NMr. Genda up against the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.45,0:13:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left shoe prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.12,0:13:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burnt shirts and dirty socks in his room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make him come under the illusion that he was the arsonist!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.29,0:13:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Genda came of his own initiative to my hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.46,0:13:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying that he had a habit of sleepwalking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.90,0:13:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.27,0:13:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he was a child, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.90,0:13:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw on TV that there are many cases, when a nervous child unable to cope with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.74,0:14:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all the excitement during the day sleepwalks around at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A psychiatrist should know something like that right off the bat, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.38,0:14:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. Mr. Genda~was loitering around nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.65,0:14:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when my house caught fire, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would never know something like that, even if I were his doctor, would I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.09,0:14:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard Genda and Soga talking on the phone, didn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.03,0:14:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the wiretap that you set up inside the underside of the telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.77,0:14:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you took out a while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After hearing Soga say. If you go to the houses on that day]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.31,0:14:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your fortune will take a turn for the better, you picked the date to set fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.98,0:14:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was change the beckoning cat key holder Genda was supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.80,0:14:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to pass out to the neighborhood that day, to the Red Rabbit Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that Mr. Genda would come to retrieve the key holders
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he finds out that he had passed out the wrong ones and that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.83,0:14:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the people would become suspicious at seeing him do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was the day that\NRyoko had called the detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.43,0:14:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you figured that if things worked out well, the detective would remember Genda
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.07,0:15:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire was set at past 7:30 pm... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.98,0:15:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Went out to drink with\NMr. Soga before 7:30 and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he also testified to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.08,0:15:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or, ares ou saying the boy next door who testified to the time of the arson is lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tissue paper is wrapped around the light bulb and taped on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's something poked in between the tissue paper too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.40,0:15:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agh! It's a match!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.42,0:15:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The surface temperature of a light bulb of 100 watts is 218 degrees...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.51,0:15:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrapping tissue paper around some ng I e a an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,moreover, poking a match between it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.44,0:15:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's not hard to figure out what will happen, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.78,0:15:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's a time-igniting device
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.52,0:15:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to set fire to your house while you are out drinking with Mr. Soga!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did the same thing to the light bulb in the storeroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.89,0:15:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,poured kerosene on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.53,0:15:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stuck a red horse between the window beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.13,0:16:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, before you went out drinking with Mr. Soga you turned on the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:06.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, 10 minutes later, the match would ignite, the tissue paper would fall to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fire would break out...\NYou shouldn't do stuff like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.77,0:16:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the boy next door as usual watches TV with the room dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.60,0:16:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the tissue is wrapped around the light bulb,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the light is still weak, so the silhouette of the horse will not project.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.92,0:16:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But after the tissue paper burns off, the silhouette of the horse is projected
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.79,0:16:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as if the arsonist had left the horse behind at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.96,0:16:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deliberately created this illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.29,0:16:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, you were probably planning to sneak in here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and burn this place down: to erase traces of you having been here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.47,0:16:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there is still other evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the stand of the key holder with the words Red Rabbit Horse on it that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.95,0:16:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoko was holding on to at the time she died!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.47,0:16:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cut part matched the leg that was left back at the fire site on 3-chome
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now all that needs to be done, is to see if the fingerprints that are on it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,match your fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.39,0:16:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cut off the stand and Kanu because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.75,0:16:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you didn't want anyone to know it was what Mr. Genda had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.72,0:17:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't want him to get caught before you kill Ryoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she knew what you were up to though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.60,0:17:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably asked the detective to come and investigate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.84,0:17:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the suspicious person\NIoitering around at night
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but found out that it was you, experimenting on the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After realizing it was you, she checked your belongings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and found the red horse and the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.22,0:17:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was convinced that the serial arsonist was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.99,0:17:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably asked us to leave, because she was planning to threaten you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.59,0:17:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She threatened to divorce me and kick me out of this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.96,0:17:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I wanted to do was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.42,0:17:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,burn the house and build a hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.14,0:17:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.57,0:17:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only if this stand wasn't found...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.74,0:17:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I didn't get deceived into a trap like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.58,0:17:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was supposed to be a perfect crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:55.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.58,0:17:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we knew from before you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.30,0:17:59.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga could've done it and so could Ryoko's older sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.05,0:18:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two also sold objects with wiretaps in them to Genda
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and? ere wiretapping him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably wanted him to believe in Feng Shui
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.29,0:18:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fortune-telling by telling him stuff only he alone knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.06,0:18:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sell him more expensive stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found out from the telephone bill that the phone was wiretapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.49,0:18:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you wiretap using the telephone line,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.11,0:18:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it has to be connected all the while so the telephone bill sky-rockets...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.78,0:18:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how can you tell that\NI'm the one who set it up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be either one of the two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.32,0:18:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still don't realize?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.09,0:18:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.46,0:18:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You understand that in order to set up a wiretap in the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you have to sneak into the house, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.50,0:18:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.67,0:18:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.04,0:18:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were to sneak into the house
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.50,0:18:58.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they would first of all remove the wiretap from the things that they sold Mr. Genda,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.31,0:19:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because otherwise, they'd be suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.25,0:19:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably came across committing this crime
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.19,0:19:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after reading Agatha Christie's\NThe ABC Murders but,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.22,0:19:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\~why-didn't you realize then that no matter how hard you think out the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who gets to laugh at the end is not the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.37,0:19:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the old man with the gray brain...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you then, Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.75,0:19:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.19,0:19:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H... no not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.52,0:19:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should be thanking these boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.20,0:19:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way...\NWhat will become of those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.07,0:19:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:20:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that they sold something outrageously expensive to Genda yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.20,0:20:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all they did was sneak\NIn to collect their wiretaps
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.81,0:20:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they didn't want to be suspected as arsonists, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.31,0:20:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll let them go after we give them a good lecture at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.98,0:20:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you believe\NGenda was innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.79,0:20:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.99,0:20:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Genda came up as a suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.91,0:20:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called him out to the park and talked to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.59,0:20:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,stayed with him for 30 minutes, but he hardly talked
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.33,0:20:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we decided to talk again some other time and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.80,0:20:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got up from the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.84,0:20:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I turned to look back at him from a distance... and saw him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.87,0:20:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,looking desperately for something in the grassy area around the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It began raining a little while after he left the bench...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.91,0:20:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It began raining a little while after he left the bench...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.65,0:20:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing the look of relief on his face,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he was looking for the cigarette butt that I threw down on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that was what caused the fire that took his father's life...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't believe that a guy like him could; set fireito anybody's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.77,0:21:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither:did I want believe he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.07,0:21:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as simple as that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.04,0:21:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you... Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes sir
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.67,0:22:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, come on, a little cheaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.44,0:22:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came all the way here to buy from you to cheer you up, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.24,0:23:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that watch is made by a famous craftsman...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.28,0:23:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.91,0:23:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if it doesn't move unless you wind it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.85,0:23:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's practically useless in this day and age, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.89,0:23:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hunk but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.32,0:23:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.29,0:23:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give me this too and as500~yenzdiscounti
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.36,0:23:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's about-it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.73,0:23:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heir,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.66,0:23:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we better hurry or we won't make it in time for the planevgoingsback .-home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.00,0:23:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we better hurry or we won't make it in-time for the plane going back home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.50,0:23:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, mister
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.33,0:23:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hurry and wrap it up:"will you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.97,0:23:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Simple wrapping will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.77,0:23:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kazuha?!
